      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 86: The debounce key mixes peer IDs and device IDs in the same namespace (`deviceId.empty() ? peer : deviceId`). If a peer ID and a device ID ever have the same string value, retry throttling for one conversation can suppress or coalesce retries for another. Use a composite key that includes both the peer and device dimensions, or at least namespace the two key types.\n\n```suggestion\n    const auto key \u003d deviceId.empty() ? \"peer:\" + peer : \"device:\" + peer + \":\" + deviceId;\n```",
