      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 98: `lastRetry_` is updated for every peer/device that comes online but entries are never removed. Over long-running clients with many contacts/devices, this can grow indefinitely even after there are no pending messages for those keys. Consider pruning debounce state when the corresponding message queues become empty, or expiring old `lastRetry_` entries before inserting new ones.",
